
[1]mesentery

   MES'ENTERY, n. [Gr. middle, and intestine.] A fatty membrane placed in
   the middle of the intestines, and to which they are attached. This
   prevents them from becoming entangled with each other by convolutions.
   It is formed by a duplicature of the peritoneum.
